WEBVTT

00:02.176 --> 00:05.005
[celestial music]

00:13.926 --> 00:16.016
[music fade out]

00:18.018 --> 00:20.020
[percussive music]

00:25.242 --> 00:27.244
[music stops]

00:30.334 --> 00:33.381
["Love Is Strange"
by Mickey & Sylvia]

00:46.524 --> 00:51.702
<i>♪ Love, mm-hmm,
love is strange ♪</i>

00:51.703 --> 00:57.360
<i>♪ Yeah-yeah,
lot of people, mm-hmm ♪</i>

00:57.361 --> 01:00.408
<i>- ♪ Take it for a game</i>
- [woman speaking inaudibly]

01:01.409 --> 01:04.976
<i>♪ Once you get it, mm-hmm</i>

01:04.977 --> 01:06.892
<i>♪ You never wanna quit</i>

01:07.806 --> 01:09.111
<i>♪ No, no</i>

01:09.112 --> 01:12.941
<i>♪ After you've had it,
yeah, yeah ♪</i>

01:12.942 --> 01:14.639
<i>♪ You're in an awful fix</i>

01:16.989 --> 01:20.949
<i>♪ Many people, mm-hmm</i>

01:20.950 --> 01:24.953
<i>♪ Don't understand,
no, no ♪</i>

01:24.954 --> 01:28.652
<i>♪ They think loving,
yeah, yeah ♪</i>

01:28.653 --> 01:30.786
<i>♪ Is money in the hand</i>

01:32.614 --> 01:35.746
<i>♪ Your sweet loving, mm-hmm</i>

01:35.747 --> 01:38.880
<i>♪ Is better than a kiss</i>

01:38.881 --> 01:40.621
<i>♪ Yeah, yeah</i>

01:40.622 --> 01:44.103
<i>♪ When you leave me, mm-hmm</i>

01:44.104 --> 01:46.280
<i>♪ Sweet kisses I miss</i>

01:48.151 --> 01:49.543
[inaudible speaking]

01:49.544 --> 01:51.502
[music continues]

01:55.376 --> 01:57.378
[unsettling music overlaps]

01:59.380 --> 02:01.250
[music stops abruptly]

02:01.251 --> 02:08.649
- [screaming]
- [scream cuts out]

02:08.650 --> 02:11.522
[high-pitched tone
rises and fades out]

02:17.833 --> 02:19.530
[silence]

02:23.012 --> 02:25.319
[birds chirping]

02:30.106 --> 02:32.934
[vehicle driving]

02:32.935 --> 02:35.024
[distant post-punk music]

02:39.289 --> 02:41.508
["Rise" by Spectral Tilt
playing on car radio]

02:41.509 --> 02:43.597
[Malcolm] So you call this
punk music?

02:43.598 --> 02:45.556
- [Liz] Oh, my God.
- [Liz and Malcolm laugh]

02:46.688 --> 02:47.557
[Liz] You're a punk.

02:47.558 --> 02:48.776
[Malcolm] Huh? I'm not a punk.

02:48.777 --> 02:50.038
[Liz] Yeah, you're
a fucking punk.

02:50.039 --> 02:52.345
[Malcolm] No, I'm not
a fucking punk. I'm a...

02:52.346 --> 02:53.911
[Malcolm] I mean,
I don't know what I am, but...

02:53.912 --> 02:55.740
- [Malcolm sighs]
- [Liz chuckles]

02:57.351 --> 02:58.569
[kisses]

03:01.442 --> 03:03.660
[Maggie over phone]
<i>So where are you going?</i>

03:03.661 --> 03:06.489
[Liz over video chat]
<i>Um... to the... country</i>

03:06.490 --> 03:08.012
<i>with... Malcolm.</i>

03:08.013 --> 03:09.449
["Rise" by Spectral Tilt stops]

03:09.450 --> 03:11.538
Uh, to a cabin, I guess.
Like, his cabin.

03:11.539 --> 03:12.930
[Maggie laughs]

03:12.931 --> 03:15.281
[Maggie] <i>A city subway rat
like you</i>

03:15.282 --> 03:16.934
<i>at a cabin in the woods?</i>

03:16.935 --> 03:19.546
[Liz] <i>Yeah, it'll be
my first time up there.</i>

03:19.547 --> 03:22.201
[Maggie] <i>Well, fuck.
It's been a while, huh?</i>

03:22.202 --> 03:23.724
[Liz] <i>Yeah, almost a year.</i>

03:23.725 --> 03:24.899
[soft music]

03:24.900 --> 03:26.596
[Maggie] <i>Wow,
that's gotta be, like,</i>

03:26.597 --> 03:28.337
<i>an unofficial record for you.</i>

03:28.338 --> 03:29.469
No, shut up.

03:29.470 --> 03:30.818
[Maggie] <i>Uh-oh,
better break up.</i>

03:30.819 --> 03:32.123
No, no uh-ohs.

03:32.124 --> 03:33.777
[chuckles]

03:33.778 --> 03:35.345
["Rise" by Spectral Tilt
resumes]

03:37.739 --> 03:39.088
What are you thinking?

03:41.569 --> 03:42.613
Nothing.

03:43.745 --> 03:44.962
[Maggie] <i>So, what are
you wearing?</i>

03:44.963 --> 03:47.356
<i>What does a person wear
to a cabin?</i>

03:47.357 --> 03:49.010
<i>It's, like, buffalo plaid?</i>

03:49.011 --> 03:50.446
[Liz clucks]

03:50.447 --> 03:52.666
[Liz] He got me a cardigan.

03:52.667 --> 03:54.276
[Maggie] <i>Is it... is it beige?</i>

03:54.277 --> 03:56.452
- It is. It is beige.
- [Maggie] <i>Ugh.</i>

03:56.453 --> 03:58.541
<i>I don't even think I've ever
heard you say "beige" before.</i>

03:58.542 --> 04:00.021
- [Liz laughs]
<i>- I didn't even think</i>

04:00.022 --> 04:02.241
<i>- you knew the bitch.</i>
- I don't even know the bitch.

04:02.242 --> 04:03.633
[Maggie chuckles]

04:03.634 --> 04:04.808
[soft music becomes pensive]

04:04.809 --> 04:06.506
[Maggie] <i>So, does he want kids?</i>

04:06.507 --> 04:09.335
[Liz] <i>I don't... uh, we--
we haven't talked about that.</i>

04:09.336 --> 04:11.424
[Maggie] <i>Don't you think
you should?</i>

04:11.425 --> 04:13.687
[Liz] <i>Uh, well, you know,
I've never</i>

04:13.688 --> 04:15.819
<i>pictured myself as a mother.</i>

04:15.820 --> 04:18.039
[Maggie] <i>So... are you happy?</i>

04:18.040 --> 04:19.432
Yeah.

04:19.433 --> 04:21.347
[Maggie] <i>And he's
still not hiding</i>

04:21.348 --> 04:23.000
<i>a wife and kids
in the basement?</i>

04:23.001 --> 04:24.785
No. No secret family.

04:24.786 --> 04:27.962
Just... him and...

04:27.963 --> 04:29.659
just the two of us.

04:29.660 --> 04:32.227
[Maggie] <i>Fuck, it is...</i>
[Maggie inhales deeply]

04:32.228 --> 04:34.099
<i>it's trippy as shit
talking to you like this.</i>

04:35.579 --> 04:38.233
[Maggie]
<i>Call me sometime, okay?</i>

04:38.234 --> 04:40.280
[pensive music becomes
unsettling]

04:58.123 --> 05:00.037
[music fades out]

05:00.038 --> 05:02.039
[water rushing]

05:02.040 --> 05:04.347
[birds chirping]

05:11.615 --> 05:13.661
[engine stops]

05:15.184 --> 05:18.187
- [indistinct conversation]
- [thud]

05:24.193 --> 05:26.063
- [lock clicking]
- [door opening]

05:26.064 --> 05:28.065
- [Liz] ...draw the line.
- [Malcolm laughs]

05:28.066 --> 05:30.112
- [Malcolm sighs]
- [door shuts]

05:32.897 --> 05:34.768
- Make yourself at home.
- Uh-huh.

05:34.769 --> 05:36.813
[descending footsteps]

05:36.814 --> 05:38.686
[door opens]

05:40.470 --> 05:42.472
[Malcolm humming]

05:44.779 --> 05:46.824
[scuttling]

05:50.741 --> 05:53.135
[ascending footsteps]

05:55.137 --> 05:56.356
[Malcolm] Oh!

05:57.313 --> 05:59.707
- [bag thuds]
- First things first.

06:00.882 --> 06:02.709
- Your masterpiece.
- Mm-hmm.

06:02.710 --> 06:04.668
- [Liz] Knock yourself out.
- [Liz and Malcolm chuckle]

06:08.629 --> 06:10.456
Come on. Ooh.

06:10.457 --> 06:12.502
[approaching footsteps]

06:13.938 --> 06:15.505
[Malcolm] Here we go.

06:25.646 --> 06:27.560
Somebody left you a cake.

06:27.561 --> 06:29.563
[Malcolm] Uh, yeah,
the caretaker.

06:30.564 --> 06:32.042
Yeah, it's a bit of a tradition.

06:32.043 --> 06:33.566
[eerie music]

06:33.567 --> 06:35.002
Her way of making up
for being so bad

06:35.003 --> 06:36.917
at taking care of the place.

06:36.918 --> 06:38.398
[distant thudding]

06:41.009 --> 06:42.357
[eerie music fades out]

06:42.358 --> 06:43.838
[Malcolm] Hey, come take a look!

06:45.535 --> 06:47.494
[Malcolm] The crown jewel
of my collection!

06:48.756 --> 06:50.758
[ascending footsteps]

06:53.891 --> 06:55.457
[Liz inhales sharply]

06:55.458 --> 06:57.764
- So, what do you think?
- Mm-hmm...

06:57.765 --> 06:59.156
[Malcolm] "Mm-hmm"? "Mm-hmm"?

06:59.157 --> 07:00.941
- [Malcolm] That's it?
- [Liz] Mm-hmm...

07:00.942 --> 07:03.422
- [Liz] It looks good.
- [Malcolm] Oh, it's good.

07:03.423 --> 07:06.599
It's good. It's great.
I love it.

07:06.600 --> 07:08.035
- You're good.
- Mm.

07:08.036 --> 07:09.645
Like, really, really good.
You know that?

07:09.646 --> 07:12.823
- Mm-hmm.
- Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm is right.

07:14.346 --> 07:16.043
[spank]

07:16.044 --> 07:18.263
[descending footsteps]

07:20.918 --> 07:22.789
[soft crackling]

07:22.790 --> 07:25.226
["I Don't Want to Play in
Your Yard" by Peggy Lee plays]

07:25.227 --> 07:27.316
[water burbling]

07:33.888 --> 07:36.456
[crows cawing]

07:37.718 --> 07:43.419
<i>♪ I don't wanna play
in your yard ♪</i>

07:45.682 --> 07:50.294
<i>♪ I don't like you anymore</i>

07:50.295 --> 07:52.384
Oh!
[Liz laughs]

07:54.648 --> 07:56.475
Who lives there?

07:56.476 --> 07:58.738
- Just my cousin, Darren.
- Hm.

07:58.739 --> 08:01.088
Not my family's
proudest contribution

08:01.089 --> 08:03.612
to civilization, but...

08:03.613 --> 08:05.092
he won't bother us.

08:05.093 --> 08:06.963
Good old weird
and cranky recluse,

08:06.964 --> 08:08.138
Cousin Darren?

08:08.139 --> 08:09.226
Actually, he just goes

08:09.227 --> 08:12.055
by regular asshole,
Cousin Darren.

08:12.056 --> 08:14.754
But, uh,
I didn't see his car, so...

08:14.755 --> 08:17.452
[Liz] Hmm.

08:17.453 --> 08:19.454
[scuttling]

08:19.455 --> 08:21.544
[sinister tone]

08:22.458 --> 08:23.589
[Malcolm] I'm gonna start
getting things ready

08:23.590 --> 08:25.634
- for dinner, okay?
- Sounds good.

08:25.635 --> 08:32.120
<i>♪ I don't wanna play
in your yard ♪</i>

08:33.730 --> 08:38.691
<i>♪ If you can't be good to me</i>

08:38.692 --> 08:40.476
[squeaking]

08:45.089 --> 08:47.396
["I Don't Want to Play in Your
Yard" by Peggy Lee fades out]

08:49.006 --> 08:50.964
[river rushing]

08:50.965 --> 08:53.010
[birds chirping]

09:00.583 --> 09:04.065
[water pouring
from spout into bathtub]

09:05.893 --> 09:07.938
[river rushing]

09:12.073 --> 09:13.247
[water splashing]

09:13.248 --> 09:15.075
[sighs]

09:15.076 --> 09:17.120
[water pouring
from spout into bathtub]

09:17.121 --> 09:18.993
Ah...

09:21.038 --> 09:22.561
Mm.

09:22.562 --> 09:24.607
[thud and creaking]

09:34.704 --> 09:36.967
[Malcolm humming]

09:40.841 --> 09:43.191
[Malcolm humming]

09:48.239 --> 09:50.111
[sighs]

09:54.724 --> 09:56.595
[sighs]

09:56.596 --> 09:58.989
[faint higher humming]

10:02.514 --> 10:03.993
Malcolm?

10:03.994 --> 10:05.605
[humming stops]

10:07.955 --> 10:10.086
[approaching footsteps]

10:10.087 --> 10:11.393
[Malcolm] You say something?

10:12.829 --> 10:15.091
No. Nothing.

10:15.092 --> 10:16.179
[Malcolm] Oh. Okay.

10:16.180 --> 10:18.442
[receding footsteps]

10:18.443 --> 10:20.227
[bathwater sloshing]

10:20.228 --> 10:22.578
[sighs]

10:24.449 --> 10:26.408
[sighs]

10:28.628 --> 10:30.759
[unsettling music]

10:30.760 --> 10:32.806
[woman vocalizing]

10:47.647 --> 10:49.649
[water rushing]

10:56.960 --> 10:59.920
[unsettling music fades out]

11:04.707 --> 11:07.622
[Liz hums "I Don't Want to Play
in Your Yard" by Peggy Lee]

11:07.623 --> 11:09.494
[high-pitched tone]

11:13.020 --> 11:14.411
[bell rings]

11:14.412 --> 11:16.719
[tub squeaking]

11:22.420 --> 11:24.595
[Liz continues humming]

11:24.596 --> 11:26.729
[exhalation]

11:28.557 --> 11:31.691
[glass squeaking]

11:32.953 --> 11:34.476
[Liz stops humming]

11:39.046 --> 11:41.004
[unsettling music stops]

11:44.791 --> 11:47.096
[insect buzzing]

11:47.097 --> 11:48.969
[sighs]

11:51.493 --> 11:54.800
- [Liz chuckles]
- [Malcolm] I'm not a punk.

11:54.801 --> 11:57.019
Not a punk.

11:57.020 --> 11:59.195
No, I don't know
what I am, but...

11:59.196 --> 12:01.850
[Malcolm chuckles]

12:01.851 --> 12:04.374
I thought you'd be happier
seeing your painting up.

12:04.375 --> 12:06.290
[sighs]

12:07.378 --> 12:09.553
You know how I feel about it.

12:09.554 --> 12:11.686
It's decorative,
and that's fine.

12:11.687 --> 12:14.645
No. No, but you made that,
you know?

12:14.646 --> 12:17.039
- [Liz chuckles]
- If I could do what you do,

12:17.040 --> 12:18.867
I don't think
I could stop myself.

12:18.868 --> 12:20.521
I'd just be doing
it all the time,

12:20.522 --> 12:22.785
again and again and again
and again and again.

12:23.960 --> 12:26.222
You--you sound
like that old joke.

12:26.223 --> 12:27.746
- [approaching footsteps]
- [Liz] What was it?

12:27.747 --> 12:31.184
If men had tits, they'd never
stop playing with them?

12:31.185 --> 12:35.842
Yeah. Yeah, well,
if men had breasts...

12:36.712 --> 12:39.018
Rome definitely would not
have been built in a day.

12:39.019 --> 12:40.715
Oh.
[Liz chuckles]

12:40.716 --> 12:43.196
[Malcolm kissing]

12:43.197 --> 12:45.765
[doorbell rings]

12:47.592 --> 12:49.116
Are you expecting someone?

12:49.943 --> 12:50.944
No.

12:53.424 --> 12:56.426
[doorbell continues ringing]

12:56.427 --> 12:57.993
[knocking]

12:57.994 --> 13:00.343
The caretaker... whatever?

13:00.344 --> 13:03.216
At this hour?
No, uh, no, of course not.

13:03.217 --> 13:06.263
[doorbell ringing
and aggressive knocking]

13:07.656 --> 13:09.876
- [Liz] Very insistent.
- [Malcolm] Damn it.

13:11.138 --> 13:13.095
["I Waited by the Chapel Door"
plays on turntable]

13:13.096 --> 13:15.271
[receding footsteps]

13:15.272 --> 13:17.012
[soft tapping]

13:17.013 --> 13:19.232
- [Malcolm] It's Cousin Darren.
- No.

13:19.233 --> 13:20.755
[Malcolm] And his date.

13:20.756 --> 13:22.017
No!

13:22.018 --> 13:23.932
[Darren, distant] I can see you.

13:23.933 --> 13:25.194
[Malcolm sighs in frustration]
I'm going to let him in.

13:25.195 --> 13:26.456
Okay.

13:26.457 --> 13:28.197
- [Darren, singsong] Malcolm!
- [door opens]

13:28.198 --> 13:30.721
[Darren] Hey-hey-hey!

13:30.722 --> 13:33.376
- [Darren] What's going on?
- [approaching footsteps]

13:33.377 --> 13:36.597
- [Darren laughs]
- Cousin Darren, Liz.

13:36.598 --> 13:38.599
- Liz, Cousin Darren.
- [Liz] Hi.

13:38.600 --> 13:40.949
- [Darren] Yup! Hah.
- [Malcolm] And, uh...

13:40.950 --> 13:42.777
[Darren] Minka!

13:42.778 --> 13:44.561
[Darren] Minka's a model.

13:44.562 --> 13:45.825
- [Malcolm] Minka.
- [Liz] Oh, cool.

13:46.826 --> 13:48.087
- [Darren] Yeah.
- Hello, Minka.

13:48.088 --> 13:49.958
- [Malcolm clears his throat]
- [Darren laughs]

13:49.959 --> 13:52.743
[Darren] Keep trying.
Yeah, yeah. Heh-heh-heh.

13:52.744 --> 13:56.399
But, uh, not a lick
of English, this one.

13:56.400 --> 13:58.620
- No speaky.
- [Darren makes a clicking sound]

13:59.534 --> 14:01.230
- [Darren] See?
- [Darren laughs]

14:01.231 --> 14:03.015
[Darren] It's Eastern European.

14:03.016 --> 14:05.278
[Darren] One of the "ania" ones.

14:05.279 --> 14:07.846
Not Transylvania,
but almost Transylvania.

14:07.847 --> 14:10.152
- Right, babe?
- Wow.

14:10.153 --> 14:13.242
- No? Who cares?
- [Darren scoffs]

14:13.243 --> 14:15.201
[Darren, loudly] She loves,
loves, loves her Molly,

14:15.202 --> 14:16.767
though, doesn't she, babe?

14:16.768 --> 14:17.943
[Darren with fake accent]
Yeah, yeah.

14:17.944 --> 14:20.206
- [liquid pouring]
- [Malcolm inhales deeply]

14:20.207 --> 14:22.164
[Malcolm] I wish you'd told me
that you'd be stopping by.

14:22.165 --> 14:23.992
- I'd have made more.
- [Darren] Oh, no problem.

14:23.993 --> 14:26.125
[Darren] We already had ours.
Couldn't wait!

14:26.126 --> 14:27.778
[Darren chuckles]

14:27.779 --> 14:31.739
Plus, we wouldn't want
to intrude on your special...

14:31.740 --> 14:33.610
night of nights.

14:33.611 --> 14:35.786
- Yeah.
- [Darren chuckles]

14:35.787 --> 14:37.659
Malcolm's a romantic one.

14:38.834 --> 14:41.618
Always has been. The slow one.

14:41.619 --> 14:43.491
[Darren chuckles]

14:49.062 --> 14:50.889
Uh...

14:50.890 --> 14:53.195
Cousin, a...
a word in the other room?

14:53.196 --> 14:55.807
- [Darren sighs]
- [receding footsteps]

14:56.678 --> 14:58.809
[Malcolm] Excuse me a minute.

14:58.810 --> 15:01.204
[receding footsteps]

15:05.252 --> 15:07.254
[men speaking indistinctly]

15:15.305 --> 15:17.046
You okay?

15:23.226 --> 15:25.272
Tastes like shit.

15:31.582 --> 15:34.324
[music distorts]

15:50.079 --> 15:51.558
- [two claps]
- [Darren] Okay!

15:51.559 --> 15:54.257
Time to go.
Upsy-daisies.

15:55.955 --> 15:58.392
[Darren] Let's let the lovebirds
have their privacy.

16:00.046 --> 16:01.525
[Darren chuckles]

16:03.092 --> 16:05.267
She's a keeper, cousin.

16:05.268 --> 16:07.313
Don't wait too long
and let this one get away.

16:07.314 --> 16:08.618
- Huh?
- [thud]

16:08.619 --> 16:10.620
Oopsies!

16:10.621 --> 16:12.274
[Darren] There you go.
You're all right.

16:12.275 --> 16:13.973
[Darren] Up, up, up.

16:16.453 --> 16:18.193
[door opens]

16:18.194 --> 16:20.980
[Darren] You're okay. Yeah.
Out the door. Good job.

16:22.155 --> 16:24.374
- [door shuts]
- [Malcolm sighs heavily]

16:26.811 --> 16:29.684
[Darren, distant]
Night-night time. Come on, now.

16:34.819 --> 16:35.907
You okay?

16:36.647 --> 16:38.693
[with fake accent]
No. Liz, Liz isn't here anymore.

16:40.129 --> 16:41.651
[with fake accent]
They had to scoop out her brains

16:41.652 --> 16:43.523
to fill out her tits.

16:43.524 --> 16:45.916
[Malcolm scoffs]

16:45.917 --> 16:48.310
See, I can only apologize
for my cousin.

16:48.311 --> 16:51.574
You know, he was charming once,

16:51.575 --> 16:55.448
but now he's just
a superficial, cowardly asshole.

16:55.449 --> 16:57.363
But...
[laughs]

16:57.364 --> 16:59.060
...not you, right?

16:59.061 --> 17:01.019
You don't go
for the 10 out of 10s

17:01.020 --> 17:02.672
or whatever the fuck...

17:02.673 --> 17:04.283
with a little drawstring
in their back with...

17:04.284 --> 17:06.938
with two or three
pre-recorded sentences.

17:07.504 --> 17:09.244
[with fake accent]
Oh, where we go?

17:09.245 --> 17:10.898
[with fake accent]
We go to clubbing now?

17:10.899 --> 17:12.682
[Malcolm] Come on, hey.

